info.name: Poker
info.attribution:
The game layout and chip design were done by https://www.reddit.com/user/96LawDawg and Discord user RogerLipsett. They are released to the Public Domain.

The library image is available at https://www.publicdomainpictures.net/en/view-image.php?image=84950&picture=poker and is available under a CC0 license.

Note to players. There are $525 in chips in the room: 300 chips each in $1, $0.50, and $0.25 amounts.
info.description: Use regular deck of 52 cards to form hands higher than opponents, or bluff them into believing your hand is higher.  Multiple rule variations and winning conditions.
